<ul><li>Pendulums of&nbsp;<b>different lengths</b>&nbsp;hangs from a supporting thread stretched between two fixed points.</li><li>A&nbsp;<b>driver pendulum</b>&nbsp;is displaced then released so that it oscillates in a plane perpendicular to the plane of the pendulums at rest.</li><li>The effects of the oscillating motion is&nbsp;<b>transmitted along the support thread</b>.</li></ul><div><br></div><div><ul><li>The pendulum with the&nbsp;<b>same length as the driver</b>&nbsp;responds much more than any other pendulum.</li><li>The response of each of the other pendulum&nbsp;<b>depends on how close its length is to the length of the driver pendulum</b>.</li></ul></div>